## Three-Layer Context Model

```
PRODUCT (stable)     docs/architect/product/     What is this? How does it work?
PROJECT (current)    docs/architect/project/     What are we building right now?
TASK (subagents)     docs/architect/subagents/   What does each agent need to know?
```

---

## Layer 1: Product Context (Stable Reference)

Files that rarely change. Architecture, design patterns, domain knowledge.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/architect/product/architecture.md` | Tech stack, system architecture, services |
| `docs/architect/product/design.md` | UI patterns, typography, component specs |

---

## Layer 2: Project Context (Current Build Cycle)

Files that change with each feature. Cleared when feature ships.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `docs/architect/project/active.md` | What we're building, goals, key files |
| `docs/architect/project/decisions.md` | Architectural decisions this cycle |
| `docs/architect/project/state.md` | Progress, blockers, next steps (auto-updated) |
| `docs/plans/` | Task lists for current work |

